From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Li Hua Qian <huaqian.li@siemens.com>
Date: Sun, 12 Jul 2026 01:03:19 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] plat-k3: main: Provide plat_rng_init stub

tee_cryp_init() calls plat_rng_init() unconditionally, but the weak
default implementation aliasing __plat_rng_init() is only compiled with
CFG_INSECURE=y. Product builds with CFG_INSECURE=n therefore fail to
link on K3 with an undefined reference to plat_rng_init.

K3 uses the SA2UL/EIP76 hardware TRNG (CFG_WITH_SOFTWARE_PRNG=n), which
is initialized via service_init_crypto(sa2ul_init), so no software PRNG
seeding is needed here. Provide an empty plat_rng_init() to satisfy the
linker.

Signed-off-by: Li Hua Qian <huaqian.li@siemens.com>
---
 core/arch/arm/plat-k3/main.c | 4 ++++
 1 file changed, 4 insertions(+)

diff --git a/core/arch/arm/plat-k3/main.c b/core/arch/arm/plat-k3/main.c
index 0fdb12ce12d6..daa26c710596 100644
--- a/core/arch/arm/plat-k3/main.c
+++ b/core/arch/arm/plat-k3/main.c
@@ -83,6 +83,10 @@ static TEE_Result init_ti_sci(void)
  */
 early_init_late(init_ti_sci);
 
+void plat_rng_init(void)
+{
+}
+
 static TEE_Result secure_boot_information(void)
 {
 	uint32_t keycnt = 0;
